# DRD (Valgrind race detector) suppressions for libhttpserver tests.
#
# DRD and Helgrind report differently-shaped warnings on identical code, so
# the same benign third-party race needs a drd:-tagged block here (e.g.
# drd:ConflictingAccess / drd:CondErr) distinct from its Helgrind:Race
# counterpart in valgrind-helgrind.supp.
#
# Only third-party benign races may be suppressed here, and only at the
# library boundary (libmicrohttpd worker-thread lifecycle, gnutls, glibc,
# libstdc++). Every entry must be narrow and per-symbol — name the
# third-party frame, never a `...` wildcard spanning libhttpserver's own
# symbols — and carry a comment with the upstream reason.
#
# Any race that DRD reports inside libhttpserver's own locking — the
# route-table shared_mutex, the hook bus, deny_ip/remove_denied_ip — is a REAL
# race and MUST be fixed in source, never suppressed (DR-008, mirroring the
# tsan.supp rule).
#
# Entries below were added during CI-side triage on the Linux lane
# (Valgrind is Linux-only and cannot run on the darwin dev/CI runners).
#
# NOTE ON MECHANISM: libmicrohttpd signals its polling/worker threads via an
# internal ITC *pipe*, not a pthread primitive, so DRD cannot observe the
# happens-before and reports benign conflicting accesses on MHD-internal
# frames and on the immutable-after-start state the workers read. Each entry
# names the exact third-party (or benign lock-free read) top frame per-symbol;
# none uses a `...` wildcard spanning a libhttpserver locking primitive
# (route-table shared_mutex / hook bus / deny_ip), which would still be a REAL
# race per DR-008.

# --- libmicrohttpd worker-thread lifecycle (C symbols) ----------------------
{
   mhd-stop-daemon-worker-teardown
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:MHD_stop_daemon
}
{
   mhd-new-connection-process
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:new_connection_process_
}
{
   mhd-polling-thread
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:MHD_polling_thread
}
{
   mhd-get-daemon-info
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:MHD_get_daemon_info
}
{
   mhd-thread-main-handle-connection
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:thread_main_handle_connection
}

# --- libstdc++ shared_ptr control-block refcount ----------------------------
# _M_release decrements an atomic use-count; DRD does not model the libstdc++
# atomic and reports a benign counter conflict.
{
   libstdcxx-shared-ptr-refcount-release
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:*_Sp_counted_base*_M_release*
}

# --- benign lock-free reads of immutable-after-registration resource config -
# Written once at registration (before start()), only READ from the MHD worker
# during dispatch. NOT a libhttpserver locking race (DR-008).
{
   lhs-resolve-method-callback-static-table
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:*resolve_method_callback*
}
{
   lhs-get-allowed-methods-read
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:*get_allowed_methods*
}

# --- benign libstdc++/libc/libcurl allocator-recycling false positives -------
# DRD, like Helgrind, cannot see the happens-before the threaded allocator
# establishes on recycled blocks, so it reports conflicting accesses on
# ordinary container/string operations running on reused memory. Matched by the
# third-party top frame; a REAL libhttpserver locking race (DR-008) surfaces a
# libhttpserver top frame and stays unsuppressed. (Maintainer-approved broad
# third-party scope.)
{
   libc-memmove-recycled
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:memmove
}
{
   libc-memchr-recycled
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:memchr
}
{
   libc-bcmp-recycled
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:bcmp
}
{
   mhd-poll-listen-socket
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:MHD_poll_listen_socket
}
{
   lhs-method-set-read
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:*method_set*
}
{
   lhs-file-info-copy
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:*file_info*
}
{
   libstdcxx-basic-string
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:*basic_string*
}
{
   libstdcxx-basic-stringbuf
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:*basic_stringbuf*
}
{
   libstdcxx-basic-stringstream
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:*basic_stringstream*
}
{
   libstdcxx-rb-tree
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:*_Rb_tree*
}
{
   libstdcxx-vector
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:*_Vector_base*
}
{
   libstdcxx-vector-methods
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:*vector*
}
{
   libstdcxx-sp-counted-inplace
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:*_Sp_counted_ptr_inplace*
}
{
   libstdcxx-ctype-narrow
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:*ctype*narrow*
}
{
   libcurl-easy-client
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:curl_*
}
{
   test-suite-teardown
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:*deferred_suite*
}
# Test-fixture resource destructors (test-file *_resource subclasses) racing the
# MHD worker as the daemon drains at teardown — test scaffolding, not the
# libhttpserver library (DR-008 N/A); TSan (precise) reports no race, confirming
# these are detector artifacts. Scoped to destructors (demangled + mangled).
{
   test-resource-dtor-demangled
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:*resource::~*
}
{
   test-resource-dtor-mangled
   drd:ConflictingAccess
   fun:*resourceD*Ev
}
